<br>
Hopefully POP will end all that.  It's supposed to provide a completely unique &quot;zone copy&quot; for every raid force that wants to raid a particular plane there much the same way AO handles missions.  'Course the only way for it to end the competition is for the risk/reward of going there to be at least as good or better than the places outside POP.<br>
<br>
The reason old sleeping ST had the hell farmed out of it on Legends was because it gave great drops for relatively little work.  The reason that the new wakeup ST is ignored on Legends is that it has much worse drops for much more work.  Truly, the only good thing that can come of waking him is to experience what might be a new wakeup script.  Until the new wakeup ST goes live, it really doesn't make sense to wake him.  It doesn't slow the competition anymore with Luclin weapons much better than SODs available, but it does piss them off in a big way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulacus1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lacus1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/02 11:39:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2773.topic&index=80>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The competitive nature of EQ ..</span><hr size=1> you'd be fooling yourself about VI if you think they fixed the script for the 4 servers who haven't awoken him yet <p>--Lacus<br>Grandmaster<br>
